==== Summary

Simple Ruby method to unindent strings. Useful for multiline strings embeded in already indented code.

==== Examples

class Profile
  def default_text
    <<-STR.unindent
      Anonymous Coward
        - Community Guest
    STR
  end
end

puts Profile.new.default_text

will output:
Anonymous Coward
  - Community Guest

instead of:
      Anonymous Coward
        - Community Guest
